itcr_course_data %>% janitor::clean_names() %>%
  dplyr::select(website, screen_page_views_per_user, average_session_duration, event_count_per_user, engagement_rate, target_audience) %>%
  tidyr::pivot_longer(!c(website, target_audience), 
                      names_to = "metric_name", 
                      values_to = "value") %>% 
  dplyr::filter(!(website %in% c("ITN Website", "OTTR website", "metricminer.org"))) %>%
  ggplot2::ggplot(ggplot2::aes(x = website, y = value, fill = target_audience)) +
  ggplot2::geom_bar(position = "dodge", stat = "identity") +
  ggplot2::theme_minimal() +
  ggplot2::facet_wrap(~metric_name, scales = "free_y") + 
  ggplot2::scale_fill_manual(values=cbPalette) +
  ggplot2::scale_x_discrete(limits = c("Leadership in Cancer Informatics", "NIH Data Sharing", "Ethical Data Handling", "Overleaf and Latex for Scientific Articles", "AI for Decision Makers",
                                                    "Reproducibility in Cancer Informatics", "Choosing Genomics Tools", "Computing for Cancer Informatics",
                                                    "Documentation and Usability", "Advanced Reproducibility", "AI for Efficient Programming", "GitHub Automation for Scientists")) +
  ggplot2::theme(axis.text.x=ggplot2::element_text(angle=60, hjust=1), 
                 strip.text.x = ggplot2::element_text(size = 8), 
                 plot.margin = unit(c(1.5,.5,.5,1.5), "cm"))

traffic_plot

long_df <- itcr_course_data %>% dplyr::select(c("website", 
                                     "totalUsers",
                                     "coursera_count", 
                                     "leanpub_count", 
                                     "target_audience")) %>%
  tidyr::pivot_longer(!c(website, target_audience),
                                         names_to = "modality", 
                                         values_to = "learner_count") %>%
  dplyr::filter(!(website %in% c("ITN Website", "OTTR website", "metricminer.org"))) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(modality = dplyr::case_when(
    modality == "leanpub_count" ~ "Total Leanpub Enrollments", 
    modality == "coursera_count" ~ "Total Coursera Enrollments",
    modality == "totalUsers" ~ "Website Learners", 
    TRUE ~ modality
  ))

Total learners from each modality

long_df %>% 
  dplyr::group_by(modality, target_audience) %>% 
  dplyr::summarize(total_learners = sum(learner_count, na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
ggplot2::ggplot(ggplot2::aes(x = reorder(modality, -total_learners), y = total_learners, fill = target_audience)) +
  ggplot2::geom_bar(stat = "identity", na.rm = TRUE) +
  ggplot2::theme_classic() +
  ggplot2::theme(axis.text.x = ggplot2::element_text(angle = 45, hjust=1)) +

  ggplot2::ylim(c(0, 4200)) +

get_plot <- function(course_name, web_traffic_overtime, publishdates, titleOI, useylab = FALSE, usexlab = FALSE, xlimMinVal = min(web_traffic_overtime$month_year), xlimMaxVal = max(web_traffic_overtime$month_year), ylimVal = 400){
  publishdatesSubset <- publishdates[which(publishdates$website == course_name),]
  plotOI <- web_traffic_overtime %>% 
    dplyr::group_by(website, month_year, target_audience) %>%
    dplyr::count() %>% #count number of times it is there so it's all the data?
    dplyr::filter(website == course_name) %>%
    ggplot2::ggplot(ggplot2::aes(y = n, x = month_year, fill = target_audience)) +
    ggplot2::geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
    ggplot2::scale_x_date(date_labels = "%b %Y") +
    ggplot2::xlab("") +
    ggplot2::ylab("") +
    ggplot2::labs(title = titleOI) +
    ggplot2::xlim(xlimMinVal, xlimMaxVal) +
    ggplot2::ylim(0, ylimVal) +
    ggplot2::theme_minimal() +
    ggplot2::theme(axis.text.x=ggplot2::element_text(angle=60, hjust=1),
                   strip.text.x = ggplot2::element_text(size=7), axis.title=element_text(size=9), legend.position = "bottom") +
    ggplot2::scale_fill_manual(values=c("Leadership" = "#E69F02", "New to data" = "#56B4E9", "Software developers" = "#009E73")) +
    geom_vline(data = publishdatesSubset, aes(xintercept = website_launch), colour = 'black', linetype='dashed') +
    geom_vline(data = publishdatesSubset, aes(xintercept = coursera_launch), colour='plum4', linetype='dotted', linewidth=1.25) +
    geom_vline(data = publishdatesSubset, aes(xintercept = leanpub_launch), colour='chocolate4', linetype='dashed')
    
  if(useylab){
    plotOI <- plotOI + ggplot2::ylab("Unique ITN Website Learners Overtime")
  }
  
  if(usexlab){
    plotOI <- plotOI + ggplot2::xlab("month_year")
  }
  
  return (plotOI)
}

itcr_course_data$webAndEnrollmentTotals <- itcr_course_data %>%
  select(website_count, coursera_count, leanpub_count) %>% rowSums(na.rm = TRUE)

  ggplot2::ylab("Bookdown Views + Coursera & Leanpub Enrollments") +
  ggplot2::scale_color_manual(values=cbPalette) +
